Part D: Website Technology Identification

Summary
The website technology identification was performed using the BuiltWith online tool.
The analysis showed that the website is hosted on a Microsoft IIS 10 web server and developed using the ASP.NET framework.
English was identified as the primary website language.
Multiple Content Delivery Networks (CDNs), including BootstrapCDN, jsDelivr, AJAX Libraries API, and jQuery CDN, were detected to improve content delivery. 
The website also uses several JavaScript libraries and components such as jQuery, Popper.js, and the Intersection Observer API.
Additionally, Facebook SDK integration and a legacy Shockwave Flash Embed component were identified. 
These technologies provide insight into the website's architecture and publicly exposed technology stack

